7:["$","article",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-white","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12","children":[["$","header",null,{"className":"mb-8","children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4","children":"Improving Recycling process of an organization with ISO 14001 EMS certification"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-4 text-gray-600","children":[["$","time",null,{"dateTime":"2026-01-02T06:31:32+00:00","children":"January 2, 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 rounded-full text-sm","children":"general"}]]}]]}],null,["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-8 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-blue-500","children":["$","p",null,{"className":"text-gray-700 italic","children":"If you wish to improve your recycling performance of your organization in line with ISO 14001 EMS, then you are at the right place. Because this article will"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Improving Recycling process of an organization with ISO 14001 EMS certification"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"If you're accustomed to ISO 14001 EMS certification, then you may recognize that when the necessities and requirements of this ISO certification are implemented in a proper way to align with Environmental Management System. With this risk of environmental impact and eventually, the magnitude of wastages is reduced. In the newer version of ISO 14001 EMS standard, the need to contemplate activities that contribute to “the prevention of pollution,” where “recycling” is included as the previous version did not cover it. It thus becomes obviously significant in certain industries that efficient recycling will play an integral part in meeting environmental and legislative needs. So, how the implementation of ISO 14001 certification can effectively improve the recycling performance and ensure the economical recycling at the same time?"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Why Recycling is important?"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"In section 5.2 of ISO 14001 EMS certification, it is explicitly mentioned that an organization’s Environmental Policy must embody a commitment to the prevention of pollution additionally as a need to satisfy compliance obligations. By doing this, you will be able to implement effective and efficient recycling practices in your organization. Be that as it may, the compliance obligations with ISO 14001 EMS standard could actually vary from sector to sector and region to region but the significance of recycling remains constant no matter the degree of changes. Imagine these situations and the implications if recycling hasn't been administered effectively, for example:"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Similar to ISO 14001 certification, another famous certification in Dubai is ISO 9001 certification. ISO 9001 certification in Dubai is based on Quality Management System (QMS)."}],["$","p","5",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"A TV manufacturer features a “take back” scheme. This means that instead of economical recycling, components are disassembled, and a few of them are illicitly disposed to a lowland."}],["$","p","6",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"A battery vendor takes back a large proportion of units sold. In order to resell those proportion of return to a scrap dealer, he cuts corners and sells it with no proper information of the destination or outcome of those probably hazardous units."}],"$L10","$L11","$L12","$L13","$L14","$L15","$L16","$L17"]}],"$L18"]}]}]
